title: Henric[us] octau[us] dei gr[ati]a Anglie & Fra[n]cie rex ... Where at this present parliament begon at London ye thyrd day of Noue[m]bre in ye .xxi. yere of the riegne [sic] of our most dred souereyn lorde the kynge, ...
author: England. Sovereign (1509-1547 : Henry VIII)
notes: Imprint from STC; Steele suggests T. Berthelet as printer.
Concerns the price of butcher's meat.
Possibly issued for the sheriffs of London, to whom the Latin writ at the beginning is directed--STC.
Reproduction of the original in the Society of Antiquaries.
